 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","title":"Port advanced trace analysis, replay, canonicalization, and minimization surfaces","description":"The current trace work is enough for kernel replay/conformance, but the upstream crate still exposes boundary/compat/causality/canonicalization/replayer/minimizer/streaming logic and richer event-structure tooling.","design":"Port these as first-class trace modules that support operator workflows, bug minimization, and advanced deterministic analysis rather than leaving trace as an internal event ring.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public trace/replay analysis modules exist with clear artifact formats and failure reporting.\\nB. Unit tests cover canonicalization, replay compatibility, minimizer correctness, and causal analysis invariants.\\nC. E2E/logged workflows show trace capture -> replay -> minimization -> summary artifact paths.","notes":"Should integrate with evidence sinks and lab tooling rather than duplicating artifact formats.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:25.654823427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:00.217498869Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","replay","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:58.577897862Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:59.386946732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:00.216716949Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:25.654823427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:29.066888768Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","title":"Port advanced lab runtime, oracle, meta-runner, network, and chaos tooling","description":"The Rust crate's lab system goes far beyond deterministic scheduling: it includes oracles, scenario runners, network harnesses, replay, snapshot restore, fuzz hooks, chaos/injection, explorer/opportunity tooling, and meta-mutation runners. ANSI C currently covers only a narrow subset.","design":"Bring over the substantive lab/testing surfaces that make upstream debugging and evidence generation powerful, with deterministic artifact production and explicit exclusions where native parity is not yet realistic.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public lab modules cover advanced oracles, scenario/meta runners, and fault-injection/replay helpers.\\nB. Unit and integration tests prove determinism and oracle correctness.\\nC. Logged e2e packs show scenario execution, oracle verdicts, replay, and artifact retention.","notes":"Dependencies: D1 and D2 should land first; network-aware lab work also depends on F/G/H.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:26.634329656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:02.727291055Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","lab","oracle"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:01.028818475Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:01.870828512Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:02.726490430Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:26.634329656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"is